h=%2F5b5fae35-3734-4689-9f01-49eb51774060%2F&expires=1781159178","videoHlsUrl":"https://vz-cfbc9d86-eae.b-cdn.net/5b5fae35-3734-4689-9f01-49eb51774060/playlist.m3u8?token=hfdJ418Kq643rXT2ipj5Bg&token_path=%2F5b5fae35-3734-4689-9f01-49eb51774060%2F&expires=1781159178","thumbnailUrl":"https://exercise-api.ymove.app/api/v2/thumbnail/5b5fae35-3734-4689-9f01-49eb51774060?library=clean","tag":"gym-shot","orientation":"portrait","isPrimary":false}]},{"id":"3adef0aa-9687-4cd0-acf6-410c9fa4ba76","title":"Cable Crossover (Mid)","slug":"cable-crossover-mid-b24dfe","description":"Starting position: Stand centered between cable machine pulleys with arms extended holding handles at mid-chest height. Execution: Pull handles together in a horizontal arc across your chest, squeezing pecs at peak contraction.","instructions":["Set cable pulleys to mid-chest height position","Grab handles with palms facing forward","Step forward creating tension in the cables","Pull handles together across your chest","Squeeze chest muscles at the center position","Slowly return to starting position with control"],"importantPoints":["Keep a slight bend in your elbows throughout the movement","Maintain upright posture with core engaged and chest up","Focus on squeezing chest muscles rather than just moving weight","Control the negative portion to maximize muscle engagement","Step forward enough to maintain constant tension on the cables"],"muscleGroup":"chest","secondaryMuscles":null,"equipment":"machine","category":null,"difficulty":null,"videoDurationSecs":null,"hasVideo":true,"hasVideoWhite":false,"hasVideoGym":true,"exerciseType":["strength"],"videoUrl":"https://vz-cfbc9d86-eae.b-cdn.net/fc636358-9e53-4892-9105-c55750e0a7f2/play_720p.mp4?token=ljtgdR38r2EgIisTb1kdfg&token_path=%2Ffc636358-9e53-4892-9105-c55750e0a7f2%2F&expires=1781159178","videoHlsUrl":"https://vz-cfbc9d86-eae.b-cdn.net/fc636358-9e53-4892-9105-c55750e0a7f2/playlist.m3u8?token=ljtgdR38r2EgIisTb1kdfg&token_path=%2Ffc636358-9e53-4892-9105-c55750e0a7f2%2F&expires=1781159178","thumbnailUrl":"https://exercise-api.ymove.app/api/v2/thumbnail/fc636358-9e53-4892-9105-c55750e0a7f2?library=clean","videos":[{"videoUrl":"https://vz-cfbc9d86-eae.b-cdn.net/fc636358-9e53-4892-9105-c55750e0a7f2/play_720p.mp4?token=ljtgdR38r2EgIisTb1kdfg&token_path=%2Ffc636358-9e53-4892-9105-c55750e0a7f2%2F&expires=1781159178","videoHlsUrl":"https://vz-cfbc9d86-eae.b-cdn.net/fc636358-9e53-4892-9105-c55750e0a7f2/playlist.m3u8?token=ljtgdR38r2EgIisTb1kdfg&token_path=%2Ffc636358-9e53-4892-9105-c55750e0a7f2%2F&expires=1781159178","thumbnailUrl":"https://exercise-api.ymove.app/api/v2/thumbnail/fc636358-9e53-4892-9105-c55750e0a7f2?library=clean","tag":"gym-shot","orientation":"portrait","isPrimary":true},{"videoUrl":"https://vz-cfbc9d86-eae.b-cdn.net/b918d74d-2aad-4f59-b17a-ea5de27aec51/play_720p.mp4?token=XQmH2joPWNapfL-eW04ynQ&token_path=%2Fb918d74d-2aad-4f59-b17a-ea5de27aec51%2F&expires=1781159178","videoHlsUrl":"https://vz-cfbc9d86-eae.b-cdn.net/b918d74d-2aad-4f59-b17a-ea5de27aec51/playlist.m3u8?token=XQmH2joPWNapfL-eW04ynQ&token_path=%2Fb918d74d-2aad-4f59-b17a-ea5de27aec51%2F&expires=1781159178","thumbnailUrl":"https://exercise-api.ymove.app/api/v2/thumbnail/b918d74d-2aad-4f59-b17a-ea5de27aec51?library=clean","tag":"gym-shot","orientation":"landscape","isPrimary":false}]},{"id":"9ddd0baa-fa4b-4f5a-8dd4-3a68dc557563","title":"Cable Fly - High to Low","slug":"cable-fly-high-to-low-22680d","description":"Starting position: Stand centered between high cable pulleys with arms extended wide holding handles. Execution: Pull handles down and together in an arc motion across your chest.","instructions":["Set cable pulleys to highest position with handles attached","Stand in center with one foot slightly forward","Grasp handles with arms extended wide at shoulder height","Pull handles down and together across your chest","Slowly return to starting position with controlled movement","Repeat the arc motion maintaining slight elbow bend"],"importantPoints":["Keep a slight bend in your elbows throughout the entire movement","Focus on squeezing your chest muscles as handles meet in front","Maintain upright posture without leaning forward or backward","Control the weight on both the pulling and returning phases","Stop when handles reach mid-chest level to avoid shoulder strain"],"muscleGroup":"chest","secondaryMuscles":null,"equipment":"machine","category":null,"difficulty":null,"videoDurationSecs":null,"hasVideo":true,"hasVideoWhite":false,"hasVideoGym":true,"exerciseType":["strength"],"videoUrl":"https://vz-cfbc9d86-eae.b-cdn.net/2fc2adab-5b3f-493b-9fea-0fb2bf330770/play_720p.mp4?token=Qqp4gbw0TRjpjzl1mP8uuQ&token_path=%2F2fc2adab-5b3f-493b-9fea-0fb2bf330770%2F&expires=1781159178","videoHlsUrl":"https://vz-cfbc9d86-eae.b-cdn.net/2fc2adab-5b3f-493b-9fea-0fb2bf330770/playlist.m3u8?token=Qqp4gbw0TRjpjzl1mP8uuQ&token_path=%2F2fc2adab-5b3f-493b-9fea-0fb2bf330770%2F&expires=1781159178","thumbnailUrl":"https://exercise-api.ymove.app/api/v2/thumbnail/2fc2adab-5b3f-493b-9fea-0fb2bf330770?library=clean","videos":[{"videoUrl":"https://vz-cfbc9d86-eae.b-cdn.net/2fc2adab-5b3f-493b-9fea-0fb2bf330770/play_720p.mp4?token=Qqp4gbw0TRjpjzl1mP8uuQ&token_path=%2F2fc2adab-5b3f-493b-9fea-0fb2bf330770%2F&expires=1781159178","videoHlsUrl":"https://vz-cfbc9d86-eae.b-cdn.net/2fc2adab-5b3f-493b-9fea-0fb2bf330770/playlist.m3u8?token=Qqp4gbw0TRjpjzl1mP8uuQ&token_path=%2F2fc2adab-5b3f-493b-9fea-0fb2bf330770%2F&expires=1781159178","thumbnailUrl":"https://exercise-api.ymove.app/api/v2/thumbnail/2fc2adab-5b3f-493b-9fea-0fb2bf330770?library=clean","tag":"gym-shot","orientation":"portrait","isPrimary":true},{"videoUrl":"https://vz-cfbc9d86-eae.b-cdn.net/4350834e-9f52-4763-988f-e38d98e91dd1/play_720p.mp4?token=BvZKTHAqdlfMS1hm95Byxg&token_path=%2F4350834e-9f52-4763-988f-e38d98e91dd1%2F&expires=1781159178","videoHlsUrl":"https://vz-cfbc9d86-eae.b-cdn.net/4350834e-9f52-4763-988f-e38d98e91dd1/playlist.m3u8?token=BvZKTHAqdlfMS1hm95Byxg&token_path=%2F4350834e-9f52-4763-988f-e38d98e91dd1%2F&expires=1781159178","thumbnailUrl":"https://exercise-api.ymove.app/api/v2/thumbnail/4350834e-9f52-4763-988f-e38d98e91dd1?library=clean","tag":"gym-shot","orientation":"landscape","isPrimary":false}]},{"id":"55bd4c71-78c6-49bd-aaaa-8c03b7528342","title":"Chameleon push up","slug":"chameleon-push-up","description":"Starting position: Begin in a downward dog position with hands planted firmly on the ground, knees tucked under the torso, and hips elevated. Execution: Perform a push-up movement while maintaining the tucked knee position throughout the entire range of motion.","instructions":["Start in a downward dog position with hands shoulder-width apart and knees tucked underneath your torso","Keep your knees bent and pulled toward your chest throughout the entire movement","Lower your chest toward the ground by bending your elbows while maintaining the tucked position","Press back up to the starting position by extending your arms","Maintain core engagement to keep the knees stable and tucked","Repeat the movement while keeping the same body position throughout"],"importantPoints":["Keep knees consistently tucked toward the chest to maintain the chameleon position","Engage your core muscles to stabilize the unusual body position during the push-up","Maintain proper hand placement and wrist alignment to support the modified push-up angle","Focus on controlled movement rather than speed due to the challenging balance requirements","This exercise combines upper body strength with core stability and hip flexor engagement"],"muscleGroup":"chest","secondaryMuscles":null,"equipment":"bodyweight","category":"Chest","difficulty":"intermediate","videoDurationSecs":null,"hasVideo":true,"hasVideoWhite":true,"hasVideoGym":false,"exerciseType":["strength","calisthenics"],"videoUrl":"https://vz-cfbc9d86-eae.b-cdn.net/1fe402ce-dc4f-4c4d-aa82-5ed5400ef49e/play_720p.mp4?token=2ap0za4IeV59wqOUOyl84w&token_path=%2F1fe402ce-dc4f-4c4d-aa82-5e